{{EngvarB|date=March 2017}}
{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2017}}
The '''2004–05 Bangladeshi cricket season''' featured the inaugural [[Test cricket|Test series]] in Bangladesh between [[Bangladesh national cricket team|Bangladesh]] and [[New Zealand national cricket team|New Zealand]].  The season also featured tours by [[India national cricket team|India]] and [[Zimbabwe national cricket team|Zimbabwe]]. The Bangladesh teams claimed their first test series victory in this season against Zimbabwe.

==International tours==

===New Zealand Cricket team in Bangladesh===
{{main|New Zealand cricket team in Bangladesh in 2004–05}}
New Zealand played 2 Test matches and 3 one day internationals (ODI) against Bangladesh in October 2004. New Zealand won both the Test matches and won all three ODIs.

===Indian Cricket team in Bangladesh===
{{main|Indian cricket team in Bangladesh in 2004–05}}
India played 2 Test matches and 3 one day internationals (ODI) against Bangladesh in December 2004. India won both the Test matches and won all ODI series 2–1.

===Zimbabwe Cricket team in Bangladesh===
{{main| Zimbabwean cricket team in Bangladesh in 2004–05}}
Zimbabwe played 2 Test matches and 5 one day internationals (ODI) against Bangladesh in January 2005. Bangladesh won both the Test series 1–0 and also won all ODI series 3–2.

