{{Infobox venue | name = Beşirli Tennis Courts | nickname = | logo_image = | logo_caption = | image = [[File:Besirlitenis.jpg|275px]] | caption = | fullname = Beşirli Tenis Kortları | former_names = | location = [[Trabzon]], Turkey | coordinates = {{Coord|40|59|50.9|N|39|40 |22.7|E|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | broke_ground = | built = 2011 | opened = <!-- {{Start date|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = | operator = | surface = | scoreboard = yes | cost = {{Turkish lira}} 20 million (approx. US$ 12.5 million) | architect = | project_manager = | capacity = 4,500 (center court) | suites = | record_attendance = | dimensions = | acreage = | tenants = [[2011 European Youth Summer Olympic Festival]] | embedded = | website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> }}
'''Beşirli Tennis Courts''' ({{lang-tr|Beşirli Tenis Kortları}}), aka '''Beşirli Tennis Complex''', is a [[tennis]] venue located in [[Trabzon]], Turkey.
Completed in 2011 at a cost of {{Turkish lira}} 20 million (approx. US$12.5 million), the complex consists of a center court with 4,500 seating capacity, three indoor courts, twelve outdoor courts and a children's court. There are also social and leisure facilities in addition to rooms for health care, [[use of performance-enhancing drugs in sport|doping]] test and press.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://trabzon2011eyof.blogspot.com/2011/06/eyof-2011-tennis-courts-are-ready.html |publisher=Trabzon 2011 EYOF |title=EYOF 2011 Tennis Courts Are Ready |accessdate=2011-07-30 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120328091754/http://trabzon2011eyof.blogspot.com/2011/06/eyof-2011-tennis-courts-are-ready.html |archivedate=2012-03-28 |df= }}</ref> The complex is the biggest of its kind in Turkey.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://trabzonteniskulubu.com/Haberler.asp?haber=devam&id=24 |publisher=Trabzon Tenis Kulübü |title=Tenis adına büyük gelişme |language=Turkish |accessdate=2011-07-30 }}{{dead link|date=July 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>
The Beşirli Courts hosted the [[Tennis at the 2011 European Youth Summer Olympic Festival|tennis events]] during the [[2011 European Youth Summer Olympic Festival]].
