{{Infobox venue | name = El Wak Stadium | nickname = | logo_image = | logo_caption = | image = [[File:El Wak Stadium.jpg|250px]] | caption = | fullname = | location = [[Accra]], [[Ghana]] | coordinates = {{coord|5|35|11|N|0|10|22|W|region:GH|display=inline,title}} | broke_ground = | built = | opened = | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = | operator = | surface = Grass | scoreboard = | cost = | architect = | project_manager = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | main_contractors = | capacity = 7,000 | suites = | record_attendance = | dimensions = | acreage = | tenants = [[International Allies F.C.|Inter Allies]] }}
The '''El Wak Stadium''' is a multi-purpose stadium in [[Cantonments, Accra|Cantonments]], a suburb of [[Accra]]. It is owned by the Ghana Armed Forces and has a seating capacity of 7,000. It was the home venue of [[International Allies F.C.|Inter Allies]], in the 2016/2017 [[Ghanaian Premier League]] season.<ref>{{cite web|title=El Wak Stadium is Our New Home Venue|url=http://www.interalliesfc.com/official-el-wak-stadium-is-our-new-home-venue/|website=Inter Allies FC|accessdate=17 October 2017}}</ref>
