{{Infobox gymnast | name = Ivan San Miguel | gender = m | image = | image_size = | caption = | fullname = | altname = | nickname = | country = {{ESP}} | regions = | formercountry = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1985|1|12}} | birth_place = | hometown = | residence = | death_date = | death_place = | height = | discipline = MAG | level = Senior International Elite | natlteam = 2010 | club = | gym = | collegeteam = | headcoach = | assistcoach = | formercoach = | choreographer = | music = | eponymousskills = | retired = | worldranking = | updated = | show-medals = yes | medaltemplates = <!-- see [[Template:MedalRelatedTemplates]] --> }}
'''Ivan San Miguel''' (born 12 January 1985) is a Spanish male [[artistic gymnast]] and part of the national team. He participated at the [[2008 Summer Olympics]]. He also competed at world championships, including the [[2010 World Artistic Gymnastics Championships]] in Rotterdam, the Netherlands.<ref>{{cite web |title=2010 World Gymnastics Championships athletes – Ivan San Miguel |url=http://gym.longinestiming.com/File/000009010200FFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFF02 |work=longinestiming.com |date= |accessdate=27 January 2016}}</ref>
