{{Infobox sportsperson | headercolor = | name = Keitani Graham | native_name = | native_name_lang = | image = <!-- name.jpg --> | image_size = <!--Only for images narrower than 220 pixels.--> | caption = | birth_name = | fullname = | nickname = | nationality = {{flagcountry|FSM}} | residence = | birth_date = {{birth date|1980|02|01}} | birth_place = [[Kealakekua, Hawaii]], United States | death_date = {{death date and age|2012|12|06|1980|02|01}} | death_place = [[Chuuk State|Chuuk]], F.S. Micronesia | height = {{convert|1.73|m|ftin|0|abbr=on}} | weight = {{convert|84|kg|lb|0|abbr=on}} | spouse = | life_partner = | website = <!-- {{URL|www.example.com}} --> | country = {{FSM}} | sport = [[Greco-Roman wrestling]], [[Track and field athletics|Athletics]] | rank = | event = | collegeteam = | universityteam = | club = | team = | turnedpro = | partner = | former_partner = | coach = | retired = | coaching = | worlds = | regionals = | nationals = | olympics = | highestranking = | pb = | show-medals = | updated = 6 May 2013 | medaltemplates = {{MedalSport | Men's [[Track and field athletics|athletics]]}} {{MedalCountry | {{flagcountry|Chuuk}} }} {{MedalCompetition|[[Athletics at the Micronesian Games|Micronesian Games]]}} {{MedalGold |[[Athletics at the 2002 Micronesian Games|2002 Kolonia]] | Pentathlon}} {{MedalGold |[[Athletics at the 2002 Micronesian Games|2002 Kolonia]] | 4x400 m relay}} }}
'''Keitani Graham''' (February 1, 1980 — December 6, 2012) was a [[Federated States of Micronesia|Micronesian]] [[Greco-Roman wrestler]].<ref>{{cite web | title = Keitani Graham | url = http://www.london2012.com/athlete/graham-keitani-1090162/ | publisher = London 2012 | accessdate = 2012-08-22 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20120827004818/http://www.london2012.com/athlete/graham-keitani-1090162/ | archivedate = 2012-08-27 | df = }}</ref> He competed in the [[Wrestling at the 2012 Summer Olympics &ndash; Men's Greco-Roman 84 kg|Greco-Roman 84 kg]] event at the [[2012 Summer Olympics]] and was eliminated in the qualifications by [[Chad Gable|Chas Betts]].
Graham was born in [[Kealakekua, Hawaii]] and attended [[Punahou School]] in [[Honolulu]]<ref name="Star Advertiser">{{cite news | url = http://www.staradvertiser.com/sports/breaking/182581191.html?id=182581191 | title = Keitani Graham, Olympic wrestler and hero to Micronesians, dies | first = Dave | last = Reardon | work = Honolulu Star Advertiser | date = December 7, 2012}}</ref> and [[College of the Holy Cross]] in [[Worcester, Massachusetts]].<ref>{{cite web | title = Keitani Graham - Events and results | url = http://www.london2012.com/athlete/graham-keitani-1090162/events/ | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20120804150847/http://www.london2012.com/athlete/graham-keitani-1090162/events/ | dead-url = yes | archive-date = 2012-08-04 | publisher = London 2012 | accessdate = 2012-08-22 }}</ref> He died in [[Chuuk State|Chuuk]] at the age of 32 after suffering a heart attack.<ref name="Star Advertiser" />
He was the first competitor at the 2012 Olympics to die.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Gray|first1=Laura|title=Is there a London 2012 Olympics 'curse'?|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/magazine-36055238|accessdate=16 April 2016|publisher=BBC News|date=16 April 2016}}</ref>
==Achievements== Graham also competed successfully in [[Combined track and field events|combined events]] in [[track and field athletics]]. {| {{AchievementTable|Event=yes|class=wikitable style="text-align:center; font-size: 90%;}} |- !bgcolor="#eeeeee" colspan="6"|Representing {{flagcountry|Chuuk}} |- |rowspan=2|2002 |rowspan=2|[[Athletics at the 2002 Micronesian Games|Micronesian Games]] |rowspan=2|[[Kolonia]], [[Pohnpei]] |bgcolor=gold|1st |Pentathlon |2702 pts |- |bgcolor=gold|1st |4x400 m relay |3:25.49 min '''[[List of Micronesian Games records in athletics|GR]]''' |}
