{{Infobox sportsperson | headercolor = lightblue | name = Terrence Dixie | image = | imagesize = | caption = | birth_name = | fullname = | nickname = | nationality = {{SEY}} | residence = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1983|10|15|df=yes}} | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | height = {{height|m=1.52|abbr=on}} | weight = {{convert|83|kg|lb|0|abbr=on}} | website = | country = | sport = [[Olympic weightlifting|Weightlifting]] | event = 85 kg | collegeteam = | club = | turnedpro = | coach = | retired = | coaching = | worlds = | regionals = | nationals = | olympics = | paralympics = | highestranking = | pb = | medaltemplates = | show-medals = yes }}
'''Terrence Dixie''' (born October 15, 1983) is a Seychellois [[weightlifter]].<ref>{{cite sports-reference|Terrence Dixie|https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/di/terrence-dixie-1.html|25 January 2013}}</ref> Dixie represented [[Seychelles]] at the [[2008 Summer Olympics]] in [[Beijing]], where he competed for the [[Weightlifting at the 2008 Summer Olympics – Men's 85 kg|men's light heavyweight]] class (85&nbsp;kg). Dixie placed sixteenth in this event, as he successfully lifted 115&nbsp;kg in the single-motion [[snatch (weightlifting)|snatch]], and hoisted 140&nbsp;kg in the two-part, shoulder-to-overhead [[clean and jerk]], for a total of 255&nbsp;kg.<ref>{{cite news|title=Men's 85kg (187 lbs)|url=http://www.2008.nbcolympics.com/weightlifting/resultsandschedules/rsc=WLM085000/standings.html|publisher=[[NBC Olympics]]|accessdate=25 January 2013|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120730233702/http://www.2008.nbcolympics.com/weightlifting/resultsandschedules/rsc%3DWLM085000/standings.html|archivedate=30 July 2012|df=}}</ref>
