{{italic title}}
'''''The Game in Time of War''''' is a collection of essays and newspaper articles written by [[Australian people|Australian]] [[journalist]] [[Martin Flanagan (journalist)|Martin Flanagan]] about [[Australian rules football]].<ref name="SMH - 13Sep2003 - The Game in Time of War">{{cite news|url=http://www.smh.com.au/articles/2003/09/12/1063341766580.html|title=The Game in Time of War|date=13 September 2003|work=[[Sydney Morning Herald]]|publisher=[[Fairfax Media]]|accessdate=25 October 2012}}</ref> The theme of the content is analysis of the relation between Australian football and the participation of [[Australian people]] in wars.<ref name="ABC Radio National - 02Jan2009 - The last quarter: Martin Flanagan on footy">{{cite web|url=http://www.abc.net.au/radionational/programs/sportsfactor/the-last-quarter-martin-flanagan-on-footy/3184932|title=The last quarter: Martin Flanagan on footy|last=O'Regan|first=Mick|date= 2 January 2009|work=[[Radio National|ABC Radio National]]|publisher=[[Australian Broadcasting Corporation]]|accessdate=28 October 2012}}</ref>
[[Ross Fitzgerald]] wrote that the book's first essay described the impact of [[9/11]] on Australian football in compelling terms, but that it was a disjointed "[[Stream of consciousness (narrative mode)|Stream of consciousness]]" in the other essays.<ref name="SMH - 13Sep2003 - The Game in Time of War"/>

