{{Infobox stadium |stadium_name = |nickname = Tully Gymnasium |image = |location = |broke_ground = |opened = 1956 |closed = |demolished = |owner = [[Florida State University]] |operator = [[Florida State University Athletics|Florida State Athletics]] |surface = |construction_cost= |architect = | tenants = [[Florida State Seminoles volleyball]] ([[National Collegiate Athletic Association|NCAA]]) |seating_capacity = 2,500 |}}
The '''Bobby Tully Gymnasium''' is a 2,500 seat multi-purpose [[arena]], in [[Tallahassee, Florida]], that opened in 1956.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.seminoles.com/trads/fsu-trads-fac-gym.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2011-07-14 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120219030331/http://www.seminoles.com/trads/fsu-trads-fac-gym.html |archivedate=2012-02-19 |df= }}</ref> It is the home of the [[Florida State University]] Seminoles [[volleyball]] team. Prior to the [[Donald L. Tucker Center]] opening in 1981, it was home to the men's [[basketball]] team as well.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.seminoles.com/trads/fsu-trads-fac-gym.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2011-07-14 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120219030331/http://www.seminoles.com/trads/fsu-trads-fac-gym.html |archivedate=2012-02-19 |df= }}</ref> The arena played host to The [[Rolling Thunder Revue]] Tour on April 27, 1976, headed by [[Bob Dylan]].
